Abdullahi Shugaba The North West Zonal Chairman, Board of Trustees of National Apex of Nigerian Farmers Cooperatives Societies (NANFACOS), Alhaji Ahmed Daura, has promised to partnered farmers to boost food production. Daura made the promise after he was appointment as the zonal trustee of the cooperative society in the North West geo- political zone in Daura on Friday. He stated that in the recent past, real practicing farmers were not consulted on issues that would boost their morale in ensuring that they produced more food to ensure security in the country. He promised to ensure that farmers accessed agricultural loans especially those who were involved in all scheme of things that had to do with agribusiness. “We will always partner the government to reach out to the farmers at the grassroots,” he added. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that NANFACOS is a non-governmental organisation that is working with the federal ministry of agriculture to ensure that farmers benefited from government agricultural loans and other incentives.(NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Gov. Abiodun to support farmers boost food productionGov. Dapo Abiodun of Ogun says his administration will help farmers and those in the agriculture value-chain businesses to boost production.December 11, 2020In "Agriculture"10,000 farmers get farm inputs support in Kaduna StateThe Agro Processing, Productivity Enhancement and Livelihood Improvement Support has commenced the distribution of farm inputs to farmers in Kaduna State.July 9, 2020In "Agriculture"Food Security: Buhari orders NASENI to deploy tractors to farmersPresident Muhammadu Buhari 